<HEADLINE>
`LIFE IN A WHEELCHAIR' PHOTOGRAPHY CONTEST TO ACCEPT ENTRIES IN
APRIL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taoyuan  County, March  27 (CNA) 03/27/07  20:24:16 (By Han Nai-
kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Development Center for the Spinal Cord Injured based in
Taoyuan County will hold a photography contest featuring the
theme "Life in a Wheelchair," a spokesman for the center said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the center will accept entries from April 1-30
and that those who are interested in entering the contest can
download applications from the center's Web site at
www.scsrc.org.tw.
</P>
<P>
He said the aim of the contest is to enhance the public's
understanding of how disabled people live their daily lives.
</P>
<P>
Works selected from the screening will be displayed at a June 3
exhibition held in conjunction with a garden party in the Sun
Yat-sen Memorial Hall complex in Taipei, according to the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He added that the first prize will be an Olympus EVOLT E-330
digital single lens reflex camera donated by Yuanyu Industry Co.,
the Taiwan agent of Japan's Olympus brand cameras, while second
and third prizes will be multifunction Epson printers.
</P>
<P>
Figures compiled by the Development Center for the Spinal Cord
Injured show that nearly 30,000 people suffer from spinal cord
injuries in Taiwan, with the number increasing at a rate of 1,200
each year. About 92 percent of these new victims will have to
spend the rest of their lives in a wheelchair.
</P>
